trans-unit.source: Previously, we auto-magically included all files within cypress/support. This has now gone away and we’ve simplified this to automatically including a single cypress/support/index.js file. That single file acts as the entry point meaning you should import or require the other support files you’d like to include. Although this is still “automatic” it’s much less magical and we’ll be updating all of our docs to reflect this. The purpose of cypress/support hasn’t really changed, just the implementation of it has. We will automatically seed a cypress/support/index.js file for you (even on existing projects). The file location of cypress/support/index.js can be changed with the new supportFile option in your cypress.json. This feature can also be turned off by specifying supportFile: false.
trans-unit.target: 以前，我们会自动将所有文件自动包含在 cypress/support 中。现在已经消失了，我们已经将其简化为自动包括单个 cypress/support/index.js 文件。该单个文件充当入口点，这意味着您应该 import 或 require 其他想要包含的支持文件。尽管这仍然是“自动的”，但它的神奇性要小得多，我们将更新所有文档以反映这一点。 cypress/support 的目的并没有真正改变，只是实现了。我们将自动为您播种 cypress/support/index.js 文件（即使在现有项目中）。文件位置 cypress/support/index.js 可以使用 cypress.json 中的新 supportFile 选项更改cypress / support / index.js。也可以通过指定 supportFile: false 来关闭此功能。

trans-unit.source: Removed {stub: false} option from cy.server() and cy.route(). Cypress will now log a deprecation warning when you use the this option. trans-unit.source: Reverted the Chrome argument that disabled RootLayerScrolling which was used to prevent the application under test from “shaking” due to a bug in versions 66 and 67. This workaround inadvertently created a different and much more severe bug in Chrome 68 that would miscalculate pointer coordinates. This led to Cypress giving confusing errors about elements being covered up on action. This is still a bug in Chrome, and is fixed in Canary but has not yet been released to the stable Chrome 68 channel. Nevertheless, removing the RootLayerScrolling flag does fix it. We did several experiments to try to ensure that the “shaking” behavior does not exhibit itself in Chrome 68. We have limited the --disable-blink-features=RootLayerScrolling flag to Chrome 66 and Chrome 67. Fixes #2223 and #2215 and #2037.
trans-unit.target: RootLayerScrolling 了Chrome参数，该参数禁用了RootLayerScrolling，该功能用于防止受测试的应用程序由于版本66和67中的错误而“晃动”。这种解决方法无意间在Chrome 68中创建了另一个更严重的错误，它将错误地计算指针坐标。这导致赛普拉斯在将元素掩盖在行动中时给出了令人困惑的错误。这仍然是Chrome中的错误，已在Canary中修复，但尚未发布到稳定的Chrome 68通道中。不过，删除 RootLayerScrolling 标志确实可以解决该问题。我们进行了几次实验，以确保在Chrome 68中不会出现“摇晃”现象。我们限制了 --disable-blink-features=RootLayerScrolling 标记为Chrome 66和Chrome67。修复了＃2223和＃2215和＃2037。

trans-unit.source:
Standard output

Standard output includes details and summaries of your tests for each spec file based on the reporter you have set. By default it is the spec reporter.

You will also see a summary at the bottom indicating the screenshots, or videos that were uploaded during the recording.

Screenshots

All screenshots taken during the test run can be found in the Screenshots of the spec. Both screenshots taken during failures and screenshots taken using the cy.screenshot() command will show up here.

Videos

The video recorded during the test run can be found under the Video of the spec. You can also download the video.

Test failures

Any tests that fail during a test run can be found under the Failures tab. Each failure is listed under its test title.

Each failure displays:

  • Test title: The title of the failed test.
  • Error: The stack trace of the error.
  • Screenshot: Any screenshots taken during the test.
  • Video: The recorded video scrubbed to the point of failure in the test.
trans-unit.target:
标准输出

标准输出包括基于您设置的报告者的每个规格文件的测试详细信息和摘要。默认情况下，它是 spec 报告器。

您还将在底部看到摘要，指示屏幕快照或在录制过程中上传的视频。

屏幕截图

在测试运行期间获取的所有屏幕截图均可在规范的屏幕截图中找到。故障期间拍摄的屏幕截图和使用 cy.screenshot() 命令拍摄的屏幕截图都将显示在此处。

影片

在测试运行期间记录的视频可以在规范的视频下找到。您也可以下载视频。

测试失败

在测试运行期间失败的所有测试都可以在“ 失败”选项卡下找到。每个失败均在其测试标题下列出。

每个故障显示：

  • 测试标题：测试失败的标题。
  • 错误：错误的堆栈跟踪。
  • 屏幕截图：测试期间拍摄的所有屏幕截图。
  • 视频：录制的视频被擦到测试中的失败点。
